"v. 抚弄，抚摸 【英】 v. 抚弄，抚摸(to stroke or handle in a tender and loving way; caress) 【记】 来自fond(喜爱的)+le →爱抚; 【同】 参考：fondness(爱好 ) v. 爱抚 = caress 【记】fond(adj 喜爱的) 【记】源自fond fondle (v.)  1690s, ""treat with indulgence and affection,"" frequentative of fond ""dote upon"" (see fond). Sense of ""caress"" first recorded 1796. Related: Fondled; fondling (1670s as a past participle adjective)."
